"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-29-Paris-Olympics-Anna-Henderson-discusses-her-cycling-medal-win-1vCn8bJVqCY-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Dan Williams  Copied  Team Great Britain's Anna Henderson has won a silver medal in cycling's Time Trial at the Paris 2024 Olympics.  She finished behind Australia's Grace Brown who took the gold. Henderson's preparation for the Olympics was far from ideal. She broke her collarbone not once but twice this season.  CGTN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dan Williams sat down with her following her medal win.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"